 various aspects of L2 lexical processing and explore different models of acquisition, processing and storage. The studies are linked by the fact that the authors have all belonged to the same dynamic and influential vocabulary acquisition research group led by Paul Meara. Alison Wray provides an overview of how Meara has led this group’s research activities in an innovative PhD programme, and John Read and Paul Nation contribute a critical evaluation of Meara’s wide-ranging contributions to the field of vocabulary acquisition research. The research studies presented here are relevant and replicable, offering researchers and teachers many valuable and critical insights into lexical processing in second language learners.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aElectronic books. -- local. 0aPsycholinguistics. 0aSecond language acquisition. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aL2 lexical processing.  aL2 vocab.  aLexical Processing.  aPaul Meara.  aSLA.  aSecond Language Acquisition.  aSecond Language Learners.  asecond language vocabulary research.1 aBarfield, Andy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarfield, Andy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBell, Huw, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoonmoh, Atipat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFitzpatrick, Tess, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFitzpatrick, Tess, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHorst, Marlise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNation, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNesi, Hilary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat